<%- include('partials/header') %>

<section class="page-hero" style="background:var(--white); padding-top:140px; padding-bottom:60px; text-align:center;">
  <div class="container">
    <h1 style="color:var(--text-dark); margin-bottom:16px;">HIPAA Compliance Notice</h1>
    <p style="color:var(--text-muted); font-size:1.1rem;">Our commitment to protecting Patient Health Information (PHI).</p>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="content-section" style="padding: 60px 0; background:var(--bg-gray);">
  <div class="container" style="max-width:800px; background:rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7); backdrop-filter:blur(16px); padding:40px; border-radius:var(--radius); border: 1px solid rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6); box-shadow: 0 4px 20px rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.03), inset 0 0 0 1px rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.4);">
    
    <div style="text-align:center; margin-bottom:30px;">
      <i class='bx bx-check-shield' style="font-size:3rem; color:var(--primary);"></i>
      <h2 style="font-size:1.6rem; margin-top:10px; color:var(--text-dark);">100% HIPAA Compliant</h2>
    </div>

    <h2 style="font-size:1.4rem; margin-bottom:12px; margin-top:24px; color:var(--text-dark);">1. Overview</h2>
    <p style="color:var(--text-muted); line-height:1.8;">The Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act (HIPAA) sets the standard for sensitive patient data protection. Companies that deal with protected health information (PHI) must have physical, network, and process security measures in place and follow them to ensure HIPAA Compliance. D Cyber Office is fully compliant with all HIPAA regulations.</p>
    
    <h2 style="font-size:1.4rem; margin-bottom:12px; margin-top:24px; color:var(--text-dark);">2. Business Associate Agreement (BAA)</h2>
    <p style="color:var(--text-muted); line-height:1.8;">As a healthcare BPO, D Cyber Office acts as a "Business Associate" to our healthcare provider clients ("Covered Entities"). We readily sign and adhere to comprehensive Business Associate Agreements (BAAs) prior to handling any PHI.</p>
    
    <h2 style="font-size:1.4rem; margin-bottom:12px; margin-top:24px; color:var(--text-dark);">3. Technical Safeguards</h2>
    <p style="color:var(--text-muted); line-height:1.8;">Our technical infrastructure is designed with security first:</p>
    <ul style="margin-left: 20px; margin-bottom:20px; line-height:1.8; color:var(--text-muted);">
      <li>End-to-end encryption for all data in transit and at rest.</li>
      <li>Role-based access control (RBAC) ensuring only authorized personnel view PHI.</li>
      <li>Secure, encrypted VPN access for all remote systems.</li>
      <li>Continuous monitoring, logging, and automated threat detection.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 style="font-size:1.4rem; margin-bottom:12px; margin-top:24px; color:var(--text-dark);">4. Physical & Administrative Safeguards</h2>
    <p style="color:var(--text-muted); line-height:1.8;">We maintain strict physical access controls to our operational centers. Administratively, all employees undergo rigorous HIPAA training upon hiring and annually thereafter. We also conduct regular internal audits and risk assessments to identify and mitigate potential vulnerabilities.</p>

    <h2 style="font-size:1.4rem; margin-bottom:12px; margin-top:24px; color:var(--text-dark);">5. Breach Notification</h2>
    <p style="color:var(--text-muted); line-height:1.8;">In the highly unlikely event of a data breach, D Cyber Office has protocols in place to identify, contain, and report the breach to affected covered entities and appropriate regulatory bodies within the timeframes mandated by the HIPAA Breach Notification Rule.</p>

  </div>
</section>

<%- include('partials/footer') %>
